<h1>Case 10 — Central Mall Management</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Central Mall Management system automates mall operations such as shop information, 
queue handling at billing counters, indoor navigation, inventory alerts, and crowd management. 
It ensures smooth customer flow and efficient resource utilization within the mall premises.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Long billing queues during weekends and festive rush.</li>
    <li>Customers struggling to find shops or specific products quickly.</li>
    <li>Inventory shortages going undetected until too late.</li>
    <li>Poor distribution of visitor density across mall floors.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Used for fast lookup of shops, product availability, and store details.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Manages customer billing queues efficiently.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> Identifies top-selling items and busiest shops.</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Provides shortest indoor navigation routes for customers.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Improves commercial infrastructure using intelligent navigation and queue systems.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Enhances consumer experience and ensures smooth crowd distribution inside large malls.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 12 — Responsible Consumption & Production</strong>
    <p>Supports efficient inventory management and reduces product wastage.</p>
</div>

